  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6cd6618 2022-08-11T00:09:12.927606Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge snapshot --diff <snapshot-file>\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nRepro steps:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nforge init repro-forge-diff\r\n\r\ncd repro-forge-diff\r\n\r\nforge snapshot\r\n\r\ncode .gas-snapshot\r\n# double the gas cost, e.g. from 212 to 424\r\n\r\nforge snapshot --diff\r\n[⠰] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n\r\nRunning 1 test for test/Contract.t.sol:ContractTest\r\n[PASS] testExample() (gas: 212)\r\nTest result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed; finished in 357.39µs\r\ntestExample() (gas: -212 (-0.500%)) \r\nOverall gas change: -212 (-0.500%)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe expected percentage change is -50%, but instead `forge snapshot --diff` displays the fraction (0.5) and appends a percentage sign",
